					<p><i>Can urban agriculture generate adequate livelihoods and food security?</i> By M. Redwood, International Development Research Centre, 2009. This report, by researchers working in urban agriculture (UA), examines concrete strategies to integrate city farming into the urban landscape. Drawing on original field work in cities across the rapidly urbanising global South, the book examines the contribution of UA and city farming to livelihoods and food security. </p>
